The paper deals with the recognition of a specific type of graph, the probe interval graph, which is motivated by an application to genomics. This suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.BIO sub-category. However, the paper also involves the development of algorithms for solving the consecutive-ones probe matrix problem and operating on PQ trees, which are topics that are typically studied in the cs.DM, cs.CG, and cs.DS sub-categories. Finally, the paper includes results that relate PQ trees for different submatrices of a consecutive-ones matrix, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.GT sub-category.
